Rating: 4
Yeah, these are fatty but they are so good! I did coat the short ribs with seasoned flour and browned them prior to putting them in the crockpot. I then sweated the onion in the same pan and deglazed it with the wine. I had more than 4.5 lbs of ribs so I doubled the garlic and added an additional can of tomatoes. I also added sprigs of fresh rosemary to the crockpot. Since other reviewers mentioned that the mushrooms didn't add much, I omitted them and didn't miss them. I skimmed the sauce well and re-seasoned it at the end of cooking. I think this is a great recipe for the crockpot and will try it without the extra step of browning the meat next time. We enjoyed them served over rice.

