Rating: 3
Delicious! I used 5.5 lbs. of short ribs. I followed suggestions of previous readers and made the following changes: seasoned and browned the short ribs, doubled the garlic, onion and parsley. Drained all but about 2 Tbsp. oil and sauteed onion until translucent, then added garlic for another 2 minutes. I used 3 cups of red wine (because of extra pound of ribs). The mushrooms added nothing; I would definitely leave them out. Cooked in a crockpot on high for 30 minutes, then on low for 7 hours, then high for 30 minutes. Meat fell off the bones. Downside of this recipe for me was all the fat. I spooned 1.5 cups of fat off the top. I would make it a day ahead or simply use pot roast.

Rating: 2
