Rating: 3
I am following up to my review from 10.3.08. I made this recipe again last week with some more tweaks and I feel like this is the way to go. First, I salted and peppered the ribs and browned them in a skillet. I poured out the rendered fat without cleaning out the pan. Then I deglazed the pan with some red wine, letting the wine boil down to half. (If you don't reduce the wine like this, the ribs end up tasting too alcohol-y.) I also threw in some fresh taragon and thyme and shallots that I had lying around. Quite an easy recipe that sort of just cooks itself.

