Rating: 4
I decided to make this at about noon, so there wasn't enough time for the crock pot. So I used my dutch oven on the stove top. I followed the directions except: I browned the short ribs (I used some w/bone, some boneless) in some olive oil after I put a little salt and pepper on them) for about 15 min. I agree w/another reviewer who said that this is actually where the flavor in braising comes from (the browning). I used the other ingredients, but added another chopped onion, three more cloves of garlic (I minced them all). After browning the ribs, I removed them and then sauteed the onions and garlic in the drippings, put the wine and tomatoes in and added 1 c of beef broth. I brought it to a boil, put the ribs back in, then simmered for 3 hours. I added the mushrooms during the last 20 min. of cooking. Served them w/the roasted parsnips, which were amazing. So, if you don't want to use your crock pot or don't have time, I promise you'll love these results!

